                    <td>Strawberries</td>
                    <td>1 1/2 pounds</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Sugar</td>
                    <td>5 Tablespoons</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Flour</td>
                    <td>2 cups</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Baking Powder</td>
                    <td>2 Teaspoons</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Baking Soda</td>
                    <td>1/4 Teaspoons</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Sugar</td>
                    <td>2 Tablespoons</td>
                </tr>
                    <tr>
                    <td>Salt</td>
                    <td>3/4 Teaspoons</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Heavy Cream</td>
                    <td>1 1/2 cups</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Whipped Cream</td>
                    <td>For Topping</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p>Mix strawberries and sugar, let sit. Preheat oven to 400F. Stir everything together. Cook for 18 to 20 minutes. Serve with strawberries and whipped cream.<br><br>Time: 1hr 10 mins <br> Serves: 6 </p>
